      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Reading the chart:** The grey line (left axis) shows the seasonal shape of\n",
        "traffic volume — typically a summer peak, January trough. The red dashed line\n",
        "(right axis) is the weekday premium: how many percent more traffic flows on\n",
        "weekdays compared to the 7-day all-day average for that month. The right panel\n",
        "repeats this for large vehicle percentage — a consistently positive weekday\n",
        "premium means HGV flows are concentrated on working days regardless of season.\n",
        "\n",
